---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Terms of Service"
	description="Terms of Service for True Recall — the rules governing use of the subscription service."
>
	<div class="legal-page">
		<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
		<p class="meta">Effective date: March 22, 2026 · Last updated: March 29, 2026</p>

		<p>
			Please read these Terms of Service ("<strong>Terms</strong>") carefully before using
			<a href="https://truerecall.app">truerecall.app</a> or the True Recall application
			(collectively, the "<strong>Service</strong>"). By creating an account or making a purchase
			you agree to be bound by these Terms.
		</p>

		<h2>1. Service Description</h2>
		<p>
			True Recall is an AI-powered spaced repetition application using the FSRS v6
			algorithm. The optional managed subscription provides access to an AI
			generation budget hosted by True Recall, so you can use AI features without configuring your
			own API key.
		</p>
		<p>
			True Recall itself is free and open-source. The subscription covers access to the managed AI
			proxy only. You may always use your own OpenRouter API key at no cost.
		</p>
		<p>
			AI generation is powered by third-party large language models accessed via
			<a href="https://openrouter.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter</a>. True Recall
			does not train, host, or control these models. True Recall acts as a
			<strong>data processor with limited scope</strong> — your content is passed through to AI
			providers and the results are returned to you. We store only your email, usage count, and
			subscription status for billing; we do not store prompts, images, or AI responses. Generated
			flashcards are AI-produced and <strong>may contain inaccuracies, errors, or incomplete
			information</strong>. You are responsible for reviewing all AI-generated content before
			relying on it.
		</p>
		<p>The Service also includes the following features that involve data processing:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Image Occlusion (AI Detect)</strong> — images from your vault are sent to
				third-party AI providers via OpenRouter for region detection and analysis.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Type-in Grading</strong> — when enabled, your typed answers and expected answers
				are sent to AI providers for semantic similarity evaluation.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>MCP Server</strong> — exposes True Recall tools on localhost (127.0.0.1) for
				programmatic access by AI assistants and other MCP clients.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Cloud Sync</strong> — an optional feature that, when available and enabled,
				synchronises flashcard data to servers in the EU.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>2. Account & Eligibility</h2>
		<p>
			To create an account you must be at least <strong>16 years old</strong>. By registering, you
			confirm that the information you provide is accurate and that you are authorised to agree to
			these Terms.
		</p>
		<p>
			Each person may hold one account. You are responsible for keeping your subscription key and
			login credentials secure. Notify us immediately at
			<a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com">pieralukasz@gmail.com</a> if you suspect
			unauthorised use of your account.
		</p>

		<h2>3. Subscription Plans & Billing</h2>

		<h3>Free Trial</h3>
		<p>
			New accounts receive a one-time trial budget sufficient for approximately 350–700 flashcards
			(~50–100 AI generations), at no cost and with no credit card required. The trial budget does not renew.
		</p>

		<h3>Pro plan</h3>
		<p>
			The Pro plan costs <strong>$8 USD per month</strong> and provides approximately 5,000–7,000
			flashcards (~750–1,000 AI generations). The plan renews automatically each month on the anniversary of your subscription
			date until you cancel.
		</p>

		<h3>Generation counts</h3>
		<p>
			Generation counts are approximate. Actual usage depends on the length of the text you submit.
			We reserve the right to adjust counts with 30 days' notice.
		</p>

		<h3>Payment processing</h3>
		<p>
			Payments are processed by <a href="https://polar.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Polar</a>.
			True Recall does not store card numbers or full billing details.
		</p>

		<h2>4. Cancellation & Refunds</h2>

		<h3>Cancelling your subscription</h3>
		<p>
			You may cancel any paid plan at any time from your dashboard.
			Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing period — you retain access to
			the plan until then. No partial refunds are issued for unused days in a paid period.
		</p>

		<h3>EU 14-day withdrawal right</h3>
		<p>
			If you are a consumer resident in the European Union, you normally have a right to withdraw
			from a distance contract within 14 days without giving a reason (EU Consumer Rights
			Directive 2011/83/EU).
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>
				For digital services that you begin using immediately, such as the True Recall subscription,
				you expressly acknowledge that performance of the contract begins immediately upon purchase
				and that you thereby waive your right of withdrawal once the service has been activated.
			</strong>
			This waiver is communicated to you at checkout before payment is confirmed.
		</p>
		<p>
			If you have not yet used any AI generations after purchase and wish to withdraw, contact us
			within 14 days at <a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com">pieralukasz@gmail.com</a> and we
			will process a full refund.
		</p>

		<h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
		<p>You agree not to:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Abuse or circumvent the AI generation budget (e.g. scripting, automation).</li>
			<li>Resell, sublicense, or share your subscription key with others.</li>
			<li>Use the Service in any way that violates applicable law.</li>
			<li>Attempt to reverse-engineer the AI proxy infrastructure.</li>
			<li>Submit content that is illegal, harmful, or infringes third-party rights.</li>
			<li>Use AI generation to intentionally produce misleading, defamatory, or harmful content.</li>
			<li>
				Use AI features to generate, process, or distribute child sexual abuse material (CSAM)
				or any content that sexually exploits minors.
			</li>
			<li>
				Submit images containing personal data of third parties — such as identity documents,
				photographs of individuals, or medical records — to AI features without their explicit
				consent and a lawful basis for processing.
			</li>
			<li>
				Process biometric data of third parties through AI features (e.g. Image Occlusion)
				without a lawful basis.
			</li>
			<li>Use AI features to generate content that impersonates real individuals.</li>
			<li>Expose the MCP Server to the public internet or use it to automate actions that
				violate these Terms.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			You are responsible for implementing reasonable practices to review AI-generated content
			before relying on it.
		</p>

		<h2>6. User Content</h2>

		<h3>Ownership</h3>
		<p>
			You retain all rights to content you create, upload, or submit through the Service. The
			text and images you provide to AI features are and remain yours — True Recall acts solely
			as an intermediary, passing your content to third-party AI providers and returning the
			results. We do not claim ownership of your content or of AI-generated suggestions.
		</p>
		<p>
			By using AI features, you grant True Recall a limited, non-exclusive licence to transmit
			your content to AI providers solely to deliver the requested functionality. This licence
			terminates when you delete the content or your account.
		</p>
		<p>
			AI-generated outputs (such as flashcards) are produced by third-party models and may be
			similar or identical to outputs generated for other users. AI-generated content may not
			qualify for copyright protection in all jurisdictions.
		</p>

		<h3>Your responsibilities</h3>
		<p>
			You are solely responsible for all content you submit to the Service, including text,
			images, and any data sent to AI providers. You represent and warrant that:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>You have all necessary rights to submit the content.</li>
			<li>Your content does not violate any applicable law.</li>
			<li>
				Your content does not contain personal data of third parties unless you have a lawful
				basis and, where required, their explicit consent.
			</li>
			<li>
				Your content does not contain child sexual abuse material (CSAM) or any material that
				exploits minors.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Prohibited content</h3>
		<p>The following content must not be submitted to the Service under any circumstances:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>CSAM or any material depicting minors in a sexual context.</li>
			<li>
				Personal data of third parties without a lawful basis — including identity documents,
				photographs, health records, or biometric data.
			</li>
			<li>Content that violates applicable law in your jurisdiction or the EU.</li>
			<li>Content that infringes intellectual property rights of third parties.</li>
			<li>Malicious code or content designed to exploit vulnerabilities.</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Content moderation</h3>
		<p>
			True Recall is a local-first tool. We do not proactively monitor content stored in your
			local vault. However, for content processed through our AI proxy or stored via Cloud Sync,
			we reserve the right (but have no obligation) to review, remove, or restrict access to
			content that violates these Terms. We may implement automated scanning for illegal content
			as required by applicable law.
		</p>

		<h3>Reporting illegal content</h3>
		<p>
			If you become aware of illegal content being processed through the Service, report it to
			<a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com">pieralukasz@gmail.com</a>. Upon receiving a
			report, we will:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Acknowledge receipt within <strong>24 hours</strong>.</li>
			<li>Preserve all available technical evidence (server logs, request metadata, file
				hashes) for law enforcement.</li>
			<li>Immediately suspend the account of the reported user pending investigation.</li>
			<li>Report to law enforcement and, where applicable, to organisations such as NCMEC
				(National Center for Missing &amp; Exploited Children) or the IWF (Internet Watch
				Foundation), as required or appropriate under applicable law.</li>
			<li>Provide information about actions taken to law enforcement upon lawful request.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>7. AI-Specific Terms</h2>
		<p>
			The Service uses artificial intelligence to generate flashcard content based on text and
			images you provide. In accordance with EU AI Act transparency requirements:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				All content produced by AI features is <strong>machine-generated</strong> and is not
				reviewed by a human before delivery to you.
			</li>
			<li>
				AI-generated flashcards may contain factual errors, omissions, or misinterpretations of
				the source material. You should verify all generated content.
			</li>
			<li>
				True Recall is not liable for any decisions, actions, or consequences arising from
				reliance on AI-generated content.
			</li>
			<li>
				The AI models used may change over time as providers update or replace them. This may
				affect the style or quality of generated output without prior notice.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Image Occlusion</h3>
		<p>
			When you use Image Occlusion, images from your vault are sent to third-party AI providers
			via OpenRouter for analysis. True Recall acts as a pass-through — we do not store, review,
			or retain the images you submit. You are responsible for ensuring that images you submit do
			not contain sensitive personal data of third parties (such as photographs of individuals,
			identity documents, or medical images) unless you have a lawful basis for processing.
		</p>

		<h3>Type-in Grading</h3>
		<p>
			When Type-in Grading is enabled, your typed answers and expected answers are sent to AI
			providers for semantic evaluation. True Recall passes this data through without storing it.
			You may disable this feature at any time and use manual grading instead.
		</p>

		<h3>AI acceptable use</h3>
		<p>You must not use AI features to:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Generate CSAM or content exploiting minors.</li>
			<li>Process biometric data of third parties without their consent.</li>
			<li>Generate content for illegal purposes.</li>
			<li>Attempt to extract training data or reverse-engineer AI models.</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>No consequential decisions</h3>
		<p>
			AI features in True Recall are assistive tools for learning. They do not make legally or
			similarly significant decisions about you. You may override any AI output at any time.
		</p>

		<h3>No training on your data</h3>
		<p>
			True Recall will not use your content to train, or allow any third party to train, any AI
			models. Your content is used solely to deliver the AI functionality you request.
		</p>

		<h2>8. Bring Your Own Key (BYOK)</h2>
		<p>
			When using your own OpenRouter API key, AI requests are sent directly to OpenRouter under
			your account. True Recall acts solely as the interface — we do not intercept, store, or
			have access to content processed through your own key.
		</p>
		<p>You are responsible for:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>All costs incurred on your OpenRouter account.</li>
			<li>
				Compliance with <a href="https://openrouter.ai/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
					>OpenRouter's terms of service</a
				> and acceptable use policy.
			</li>
			<li>Any data processed through your key, including compliance with applicable data
				protection law.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			True Recall is not liable for charges, data processing, or service issues related to your
			own API key.
		</p>

		<h2>9. Cloud Sync</h2>
		<p>
			Cloud Sync is an optional feature that, when available and enabled, synchronises flashcard
			data to Supabase servers in the EU (AWS eu-central-1).
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>You may enable or disable Cloud Sync at any time.</li>
			<li>The content moderation terms in Section 6 apply to cloud-synced data.</li>
			<li>
				If we detect a violation of the User Content policy in cloud-synced data, we may
				suspend sync access and notify you.
			</li>
			<li>
				You may export your data at any time via the export feature before disabling
				sync or deleting your account.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>10. MCP Server</h2>
		<p>
			The True Recall MCP Server exposes True Recall tools on localhost (127.0.0.1) for programmatic
			access by AI assistants and other MCP clients.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>The MCP Server is provided for personal, local use only. You must not expose it to
				the public internet.</li>
			<li>You are responsible for any third-party MCP clients you connect and for the data
				they transmit.</li>
			<li>True Recall is not liable for actions taken by third-party MCP clients or for data
				they process.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>11. Service Availability</h2>
		<p>
			The Service is provided "<strong>as is</strong>" without any uptime guarantee at the current
			price tier. We aim for high availability but do not warrant uninterrupted access. Planned
			maintenance will be announced where possible. We are not liable for losses caused by
			temporary unavailability.
		</p>

		<h2>12. Intellectual Property</h2>
		<p>
			<strong>Your content:</strong> Subject to the User Content terms in Section 6, you own all
			flashcards, notes, and other content you create with True Recall. You grant True Recall a
			limited licence to transmit that content solely to deliver the AI features you request.
			True Recall does not store, review, or claim any rights over the content you pass through
			to AI providers.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Our property:</strong> True Recall owns the application code, prompt engineering, API
			infrastructure, and all related intellectual property. The application is released under an
			open-source licence (see the repository). The managed subscription service is proprietary.
		</p>

		<h2>13. Limitation of Liability</h2>
		<p>
			To the maximum extent permitted by law, True Recall's total liability to you for any claims
			arising from these Terms or the Service shall not exceed the amounts you paid us in the
			<strong>3 months</strong> preceding the claim.
		</p>
		<p>
			We are not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages, including loss of data
			or lost profits, even if advised of the possibility of such damages. In particular, True
			Recall is not liable for: (a) any content you choose to submit to AI providers through the
			Service; (b) the outputs generated by third-party AI models; (c) any data processing
			performed by AI providers on content you submitted.
		</p>
		<p>
			Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion of implied warranties or limitation of
			liability — in those jurisdictions our liability is limited to the fullest extent permitted
			by law.
		</p>

		<h2>14. Indemnification</h2>
		<p>
			You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless True Recall and its operator from any
			claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees)
			arising from:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Your violation of these Terms.</li>
			<li>
				Your User Content, including any claim that content you submitted to AI features
				infringes third-party intellectual property rights, violates applicable data protection
				law, or contains illegal material.
			</li>
			<li>
				Your use of AI features in violation of the Acceptable Use (Section 5) or AI-Specific
				Terms (Section 7).
			</li>
			<li>Your use of a personal API key (BYOK) under Section 8.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>This indemnification obligation survives termination of your account.</p>

		<h2>15. Termination</h2>
		<p>
			You may delete your account at any time by contacting
			<a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com">pieralukasz@gmail.com</a>.
		</p>
		<p>
			We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms, with or
			without prior notice. Grounds for immediate termination without notice include: submission
			of CSAM, use of the Service for clearly illegal purposes, or repeated violations of the
			User Content policy.
		</p>
		<p>
			In the event we discontinue the Service entirely, we will provide at least
			<strong>30 days' notice</strong> by email and issue prorated refunds for prepaid
			subscription periods.
		</p>

		<h2>16. Changes to These Terms</h2>
		<p>
			We may update these Terms from time to time. For material changes, we will notify you by
			email at least <strong>14 days</strong> before the new Terms take effect. Continued use of
			the Service after that date constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms. If you do not agree,
			you may cancel your subscription and delete your account before the effective date.
		</p>

		<h2>17. Governing Law & Disputes</h2>
		<p>
			These Terms are governed by the laws of <strong>Poland</strong> and, where applicable,
			European Union law. Consumer rights granted by EU law are not affected by the choice of
			Polish law.
		</p>
		<p>
			We encourage resolving disputes by email first (<a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com"
				>pieralukasz@gmail.com</a
			>). If a dispute cannot be resolved informally, it shall be submitted to the competent
			Polish courts. EU consumers may also use the
			<a
				href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr"
				target="_blank"
				rel="noopener">EU Online Dispute Resolution platform</a
			>.
		</p>

		<h2>18. Force Majeure</h2>
		<p>
			Neither party shall be liable for failure or delay in performance due to causes beyond its
			reasonable control, including but not limited to: natural disasters, war, terrorism,
			pandemics, government actions, internet or infrastructure failures, or third-party service
			provider outages (including AI model providers). This does not affect your right to cancel
			your subscription.
		</p>

		<h2>19. Severability</h2>
		<p>
			If any provision of these Terms is found to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable by a
			court of competent jurisdiction, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and
			effect. The invalid provision shall be modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it
			valid and enforceable while preserving its original intent.
		</p>

		<h2>20. Entire Agreement</h2>
		<p>
			These Terms, together with the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, constitute the entire
			agreement between you and True Recall regarding the Service. They supersede all prior or
			contemporaneous agreements, representations, and understandings, whether written or oral.
		</p>

		<h2>21. Contact</h2>
		<p>
			Questions about these Terms? Email us at
			<a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com">pieralukasz@gmail.com</a>.
		</p>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.legal-page {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding-top: 2.5rem;
		padding-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.legal-page h1 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
	}

	.meta {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-4);
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.legal-page h2 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 2.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-1);
	}

	.legal-page h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-top: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
	}

	.legal-page p,
	.legal-page li {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
		line-height: 1.7;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
	}

	.legal-page p + p {
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
	}

	.legal-page ul {
		margin: 0.625rem 0 0.625rem 1.25rem;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.375rem;
	}

	.legal-page a {
		color: var(--sl-color-accent-high);
	}
</style>
